Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}(minced, use 1 clove). Chop @parsley{¼%ounce}(chopped). Trim @green beans{6%ounce}(trimmed). Halve and peel @yellow onion{1}(peeled and halved). Using a #box grater{}, grate one half into a #large bowl{} (feel free to use the other half as you like).

Add garlic, parsley, @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, @ground beef{10%ounce}, and @salt{½%tsp} to same bowl. Season with @pepper{}, then mix with hands to combine. Form into two 1-inch-tall loaves and place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. In a #small bowl{}, mix @balsamic vinegar{2%tablespoon} and @ketchup{1%unit}, then brush onto meatloaves. Bake in oven until no longer pink in center, about ~{25%minutes} total.

Peel and chop @sweet potatoes{12%ounce}(peeled and cubed) into ½-inch cubes. Place in a #large pot{} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and enough water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until easily pierced with a fork, about ~{10%minutes}. Drain and return to #pot{}.

After meatloaves have baked 10 minutes, remove from oven. Toss green beans on same baking sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. (TIP: Use tongs to avoid burning your hands.) Return to oven and bake until meatloaves are cooked through and green beans are slightly browned, about ~{15%minutes} more.

Mash sweet potato in #pot{} with a fork or #potato masher{} until smooth. (TIP: If potatoes have cooled, quickly reheat over medium-low heat.) Add @butter{1%tablespoon} and @honey{½%ounce}. Continue mashing to combine. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

When meatloaves and green beans are done, sprinkle @almonds{1%ounce} over green beans and toss to combine. Divide meatloaves between plates and serve with sweet potato mash and green beans on the side.